column95: My best day was my most stressful. A Friday night with deadlines looming my shift was missing half of our people due to the round of layoffs that hit that morning with no notice from leadership. Those of us who were left had no choice but to dive in and get everything done that needed to get done. By the end of my shift everything was done that absolutely needed to get done ahead of each deadline and I left with an exhausted satisfaction of what we can do when we absolutely have to. That being said, I would not recommend that on any regular basis.

column94: Recognition to employees who go beyond their expectations besides years employed by company. Also a day off on your birthday with pay, or if you want to work that day you just get an extra straight hours on your paycheck.  I can't tell you how much this means to an employee - worked at a place that did this and for me I felt appreciated and recognized for what I do.  I think I mentioned this before on a survey years ago but nothing ever gets done or explained.  And of course this is just my suggestion and opinion.   And although it is appreciated at Christmas with a $25.00 gift card, these days you can't do much with $25.00.  And all employees should get bonuses according to their accomplishments.  The little people like me, I've been here 13 years and only got 1 bonus two years ago.  People in my office gets bonuses and it is very  hurtful when you are part of that team and you get nothing.  I just suggesting a few things that some people thinks matter to them, me being one of them, but please know I love my job bonuses or not.  I'm truly grateful I am a Lamons employee and Blessed every day I can come to work.
